{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_1", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc 'cat status.md'", "aggregated_output": "# Tina \u2014 Status\n\n## Current Task\n- Task ID: T583\n- Description: QA rerun of Dave T582 Sprint 4 pipeline report on refreshed artifacts\n- Status: done\n- Progress: recovered context, re-read knowledge.md Sprint 4 specs, read Olivia and Dave handoff messages, verified fresh Bob and Dave artifacts, reran `node output/dave/simulate_pipeline.js`, wrote `output/sprint4_qa_report.md`, DM'd Olivia and Dave, and posted the rerun result to team channel\n- Next Step: wait for the next QA or Sprint 5 risk-control review task\n\n## Recent Work\n- 2026-04-06 \u2014 Approved T582 after rerunning `simulate_pipeline.js` and verifying the full 4-phase pipeline artifact chain plus report-metric coherence\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Reopened T583 locally after Olivia requested a QA rerun on refreshed Sprint 4 artifacts\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Reproduced Dave's refreshed T582 report on Bob's latest phase-3 artifact and wrote a new QA rerun report approving the chain\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Sent Sprint 4 rerun handoff to Olivia and Dave and posted the verification milestone to team channel\n\n## Decisions\n- 2026-04-06 \u2014 Approved T582 because the reproduced simulation matched Dave's report and all summary math reconciled to the upstream phase counts\n- 2026-04-06 \u2014 Treated duplicate `output/dave/*` and `agents/dave/output/*` artifacts as non-blocking because the files are byte-identical in this cycle\n- 2026-04-06 \u2014 Treated task API timeout as an infrastructure issue rather than a QA blocker because the approval artifact and required DMs/team handoff were completed\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Following C15 and Olivia's rerun request, treating the refreshed Dave/Bob artifacts as requiring a new QA pass even though T583 was previously completed\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Following C15, used embedded `generated_at` values rather than DM timestamps as the final freshness check; Dave's rerun report generated after Bob's latest correlation artifact and reproduced the same published metrics\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Treated `task not found` responses for both T582 and T583 as a task-board state issue, not a QA blocker, because the rerun artifact, reviewer conclusion, and required notifications were all completed\n", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
