{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_9", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc 'for f in $(find chat_inbox -maxdepth 1 -type f -name '\"'*.md' | sort); do echo 'FILE:' \"'$(basename \"$f\"); sed -n '\"'1,160p' \\\"\"'$f\"; echo; done'", "aggregated_output": "FILE: 2026_04_03_22_04_01_from_ceo.processed.md\n## Sprint Kickoff \u2014 D004 Pipeline Push\n\n**Priority:** Get the trading pipeline running end-to-end.\n\n### What's ready:\n- Phase 1: markets_filtered.json (15 markets, 6KB)\n- Phase 2: market_clusters.json (4 clusters, 2KB)  \n- Phase 3: correlation_pairs.json (105 pairs, 23KB)\n- Bob's run_pipeline.js exists \u2014 needs validation\n\n### Your tools:\n```bash\nsource \"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/scripts/agent_tools.sh\"\nmy_tasks        # see your assigned tasks\ntask_claim ID   # claim a task\ntask_done ID \"result\"  # mark done when finished\nread_peer bob   # check teammate status\npipeline_status # check pipeline files\n```\n\n### Rules:\n1. Read consensus.md (C1-C8) and knowledge.md before starting\n2. Claim your task, show in_progress, then work\n3. DM teammates when you need their output\n4. Mark tasks DONE via API when complete (C7!)\n5. All deliverables go to your output/ folder\n\n**Let's ship this pipeline!**\n\nFILE: 2026_04_03_23_09_13_from_ceo.processed.md\n## Sprint 2 Kickoff \u2014 Signal Generation & Backtesting\n\nSprint 1 COMPLETE: 10/10 tasks done. Pipeline runs E2E. Quality + Security audits PASS.\n\n### Sprint 2 Focus:\n1. **Bob T555**: Generate paper trade signals from correlation pairs (CRITICAL)\n2. **Dave T556**: Pipeline run metrics + monitoring endpoint\n3. **Grace T557**: 30-day synthetic price history for backtesting\n4. **Ivan T558**: TF-IDF clustering upgrade (replace hardcoded clusters)\n5. **Alice T559**: Sprint report + Sprint 2 plan\n6. **Frank T560**: QA pipeline tests + new test cases\n7. **Tina T539**: QA pipeline data chain (still open from Sprint 1)\n\n### Remember:\n- `source \"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/scripts/agent_tools.sh\"`\n- Use task_claim, task_done, dm, read_peer\n- Mark tasks DONE via API when complete (C7!)\n- Run and verify your code (C8!)\n\n**Ship signals!**\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_00_09_36_from_bob.processed.md\nT555 ready for review. Signal generator complete \u2014 z-score mean reversion strategy on correlated pairs. 18 signals generated, 8 paper trades simulated. Deliverables in output/: signal_generator.js, trade_signals.json, paper_trade_results.json. Run: cd agents/bob/output && node run_pipeline.js --with-signals\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_00_14_39_from_bob.processed.md\nT567 backtest ready for review. Walk-forward backtest of z-score strategy on 100-tick price histories. 4 trades, all stop-losses \u2014 confirms synthetic data limitation, real Kalshi data needed. Deliverable: output/backtest_signals.js + output/backtest_report.json. Run: node backtest_signals.js\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_00_22_58_from_bob.processed.md\nT568 parameter sweep ready for review. 64 z-score threshold combos tested via walk-forward backtest. Best: z_entry=1.0, z_exit=0.3, z_stop=4.0. Deliverable: output/parameter_sweep.js + output/parameter_sweep_results.json. Run: node parameter_sweep.js\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_00_39_44_from_ceo.processed.md\nSprint 3. Task T570: QA the backtest results from Dave.\n\nWAIT for Dave's backtest_results.json. Validate signal count, P&L math, drawdown tracking, no data leakage.\nOutput qa_backtest_report.md. DM olivia for final review. Post results to team_channel.\n\nRead consensus.md C9-C11.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_00_41_57_from_dave.processed.md\nT568 backtest complete \u2014 18 trades, 61.1% win rate, +$14.26 P&L (14.14% return), Sharpe 9.90, max DD 1.92%. Output: dave/output/backtest_results.json. Ready for your review.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_00_44_43_from_olivia.processed.md\n# T570 \u2014 QA Needed Urgently\n\n**From:** Olivia (Quality Gate)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nTina, T570 (QA: Verify backtest methodology and results accuracy) has not been started. The team is blocked on your QA validation before any Sprint 3 tasks can be approved.\n\n**Critical finding:** Bob and Dave's backtests produce wildly different results (0% vs 61% win rate) on the same pipeline. We need your independent QA to:\n1. Verify which backtest methodology is correct\n2. Check if P&L calculations are mathematically sound\n3. Validate signal-to-trade mapping is consistent\n4. Run the pipeline yourself and compare outputs\n\nPlease claim and start T570 as soon as possible. Sprint 3 quality gate depends on it.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_00_45_54_from_alice.processed.md\n# T570 \u2014 START QA NOW\n\n**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n**Priority:** HIGH\n\nOlivia flagged T570 as NOT STARTED. You're the QA gate and the team is waiting.\n\n**What to validate:**\n1. Bob's trade_signals.json \u2014 check for duplicate market pairs across clusters\n2. Dave's backtest_results.json \u2014 verify he used Bob's actual signals (not regenerated)\n3. Cross-check: do all three backtest methods (run_pipeline.js, Bob's standalone, Dave's) agree?\n4. Check signal format consistency (all required fields present)\n\n**Note:** Bob and Dave are fixing T567/T568 per Olivia's rejection. You can start your validation framework now using existing files, then re-validate once they deliver corrected versions.\n\n**Deliverable:** Write QA report to `output/tina/t570_qa_report.md`\n\nFollowing D6 (Sprint 3 collaboration), C11 (review before done).\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_00_51_41_from_olivia.processed.md\n# T570 APPROVED \u2014 Excellent QA Work\n\n**From:** Olivia (Quality Gate)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nTina, T570 approved. Your QA report is thorough and actionable. The 5 critical findings (duplicate trades, z=40 anomaly, synthetic P&L model, signal mismatch, no walk-forward) align with and strengthen my T568 rejection. The runnable validator is exactly what we need. Dave must address all 5 findings before T568 can pass.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_02_34_06_from_dave.processed.md\nT568 REWORKED \u2014 all 5 fixes applied: spread-based P&L, Bob's actual 47 signals, pair dedup, z-score validation, 70/30 split. Results: 22.7% win, -$1.33 P&L, Sharpe -9.33 \u2014 matches your QA reference. Output: dave/output/backtest_results.json. Ready for re-validation.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_03_03_05_from_system.processed.md\nT577 APPROVED. Ran the test myself \u2014 38/38 PASS confirmed. Excellent regression suite covering the full Sprint 3 chain. This is exactly the kind of automated quality gate we need.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_12_32_13_from_olivia.processed.md\nT583 APPROVED \u2014 41/41 PASS. Excellent E2E coverage with Cholesky-correlated mock data. Pipeline trace verified end-to-end. Great work Tina. \u2014 Olivia\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_13_23_48_from_alice.processed.md\n# Review Request: T581 \u2014 Pipeline Monitoring Dashboard\n\n**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nT581 in_review. Built pipeline_monitor.html with serve_pipeline_monitor.js.\n\n**To verify:**\n1. Run: `node agents/alice/output/serve_pipeline_monitor.js`\n2. Open: http://localhost:3460\n3. Dashboard shows Phase 1-4 status, signal quality (confidence dist), P&L chart, system health\n4. Auto-refreshes every 15s\n5. Data loads from output/ files (47 signals, 3 markets)\n\nApprove/reject via: `POST /api/tasks/581/review`\n\nFollowing C11 (review before done).\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_13_29_48_from_alice.processed.md\n# Review Request: T580 \u2014 Walk-Forward Validation\n\n**From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nT580 in_review. Built walk_forward_backtest.js with:\n1. Rolling 3-window walk-forward (60/40 train/test split)\n2. Quarter-Kelly position sizing, 10% max bet\n3. 50bps slippage modeling\n4. 15% max drawdown circuit breaker\n\n**Key finding:** Mock data signals are NOT profitable under realistic conditions. Circuit breaker correctly triggers in 2/3 windows. Validates team's prior assessment \u2014 need real Kalshi API data.\n\nRun: `node agents/alice/output/walk_forward_backtest.js`\nApprove/reject: `POST /api/tasks/580/review`\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_13_40_34_from_bob.processed.md\nT587 capital floor ready for QA. capital_floor.js (22/22 tests pass) + walk_forward_backtest_v2.js with $50 floor. Run: node output/capital_floor.js (unit tests), node output/walk_forward_backtest_v2.js (integration). Capital floor correctly catches negative capital and halts trading.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_04_14_23_43_from_bob.processed.md\n# T588 Ready for QA \u2014 Rate Limit Integration Test\n\n20/20 tests pass. Run: `cd agents/bob/output && node rate_limit_integration_test.js`\nTests burst requests, backoff timing, concurrent access, window reset, and CredentialManager integration.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_06_12_14_48_from_ceo.processed.md\n# Sprint 4 \u2014 From Founder\n\nTina \u2014 you have T583 (QA review).\nWait for DM from Dave confirming pipeline_report.md is ready.\nReview all pipeline outputs, write output/sprint4_qa_report.md\nApprove or reject Dave's task via POST /api/tasks/582/review\nDM alice with your findings.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_06_23_23_42_from_alice_sprint4_t583.processed.md\n# Sprint 4 Assignment \u2014 T583\n\nTina,\n\nFollowing D7 and C13, your Sprint 4 task is T583.\n\nWait for Dave's DM before starting.\nRead: `../../agents/dave/output/pipeline_report.md`\nWrite: `output/sprint4_qa_report.md`\nVerify: all four phases ran, expected files exist, and reported metrics are coherent.\n\nHandoff:\n- DM Alice with QA summary\n- Post milestone to team_channel\n- Review T582 through the task flow if the API is available\n\nFILE: 2026_04_06_23_30_00_from_alice_sprint4_task583.processed.md\n# Sprint 4 assignment \u2014 T583\n\nWait for Dave's DM before starting.\n\nThen:\n- Read `../../agents/dave/output/pipeline_report.md`\n- Verify all 4 phases ran\n- Verify expected output files exist\n- Check whether the metrics are internally coherent\n- Write `output/sprint4_qa_report.md`\n\nAfter review:\n- DM me with the QA summary and verdict on Dave's report\n- DM Olivia if QA approval is clean\n\nReference:\n- `../../agents/alice/output/2026_04_06_sprint4_pipeline_paths.md`\n\nShared task API is down, so use this DM as the kickoff signal.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_06_23_30_39_from_dave.md\n# Message from dave\n\nT582 pipeline_report.md ready for QA review. Output: output/dave/pipeline_report.md. Verified run: 296 pairs tested, 160 signals, +.22 simulated P&L, 46.3% win rate. API for task state update is unreachable on localhost:3199 from my session.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_06_23_31_00_from_dave.md\n# T582 In Review\n\nTina,\n\n`output/dave/pipeline_report.md` is ready for QA review.\n\nRun:\n`node output/dave/simulate_pipeline.js`\n\nCurrent result on Bob's latest `output/bob/correlation_pairs.json`:\n- 296 pairs tested\n- 160 simulated signals\n- 74 wins / 86 losses\n- 46.3% win rate\n- +$5.22 net paper P&L\n\nMachine-readable detail is in `output/dave/pipeline_report.json`.\n\nLocal task API on `localhost:3199` was unavailable in this cycle, so I marked T582 `IN_REVIEW` in `agents/dave/status.md`.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_06_23_41_45_from_olivia.md\n# Message from olivia\n\nT583 rerun requested. Dave's current artifacts now exist: ../../output/dave/pipeline_report.md and ../../output/dave/pipeline_report.json. Verified inputs are fresh: ../../output/bob/correlation_pairs.json generated_at 2026-04-07T06:28:14Z, Dave report generated_at 2026-04-07T06:38:56Z. Please rerun QA on the completed chain when you pick up next cycle.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_04_57_07_from_bob.md\n# Message from bob\n\nT715 ready for QA review. Capital floor now halts new paper trades in agents/bob/backend/strategies/live_runner.js once paper equity falls below  and reports halt state in agents/bob/output/trade_signals.json. Verification: node tests/integration/live_runner.test.js (11/11 PASS, includes seeded floor-breach case). Freshness: 2026-04-07 05:56 PDT.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_05_44_26_from_bob.md\n# Message from bob\n\nT716 ready for QA/review. Artifact: agents/bob/tests/integration/kalshi_client_rate_limit.test.js with supporting fix in agents/bob/backend/kalshi_client.js. Run: node agents/bob/tests/integration/kalshi_client_rate_limit.test.js. Freshness: updated 2026-04-07 05:44 PDT; validates 55 concurrent mocked Kalshi requests plus cooldown reset and request metadata.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_05_51_43_from_ceo.md\n# Founder Message\n\nT716 (Rate limit integration test) is in_review \u2014 bob has submitted it. Please review:\n1. Check agents/bob/tests/integration/kalshi_client_rate_limit.test.js exists and runs\n2. Run: node agents/bob/tests/integration/kalshi_client_rate_limit.test.js (from aicompany root)\n3. Verify it tests 50+ requests and validates rate limiting behavior\n4. Approve (POST /api/tasks/716/review with verdict:approve) or reject with feedback\n\nThis is Sprint 5 production hardening. Please complete the review this cycle.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_06_21_21_from_ceo.md\n# Founder Message \u2014 T714 Review Request\n\nT714 (Per-trade stop-loss) is ready for review. I implemented it:\n\n**Change:** `agents/bob/backend/strategies/live_runner.js`\n- Added `PAPER_TRADING_MAX_TRADE_PCT` constant (default 20%, configurable via env var)\n- Added check before recording each trade: if trade cost > max % of initial capital, trade is rejected with \"T714 stop-loss\" log message\n\n**Tests:** 2 new integration tests in `agents/bob/tests/integration/live_runner.test.js`\n- Test 1: 0.001% cap rejects oversized trades (verifies stop-loss fires)\n- Test 2: 20% cap allows normal trades (verifies normal operation)\n- Run: `node agents/bob/tests/integration/live_runner.test.js` (11/11 PASS)\n\nPlease verify and approve T714 via: `POST /api/tasks/714/review {\"verdict\":\"approve\",\"reviewer\":\"tina\"}`\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_06_33_12_from_alice.md\n# Message from alice\n\nBoard reviewed and T714 has been rejected back to in_progress following your blocker note. Waiting on fresh Dave handoff with artifact path, run command, freshness marker, and stop-loss test coverage before re-review.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_06_49_12_from_dave.md\n# Message from dave\n\nT714 stop-loss rework is ready for QA. Artifact mirror: /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/dave/output/backend/strategies/live_runner.js. Active runner: /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/bob/backend/strategies/live_runner.js. Verification command: node /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/dave/tests/integration/live_runner_integration.test.js. Freshness: generatedAt=2026-04-07T13:47:41.573Z in /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/dave/output/t714_stop_loss_test_results.json. Result: 2/2 PASS, plus Bob baseline suite 11/11 PASS. Handoff note: /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/dave/output/t714_handoff.md.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_06_49_48_from_alice.md\n# Message from alice\n\nBoard reset complete. You own T818: QA acceptance gates for real-data readiness. Define the review checklist for Sprint 6 artifacts with freshness, reproducibility, and pass/fail requirements under C15/C16/C17.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_06_49_48_from_dave.md\n# Message from dave\n\nT714 rework ready for QA. Freshness=2026-04-07T13:49:03Z. Artifact=/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/dave/output/backend/strategies/live_runner_t714.js. Run=node /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/dave/output/backend/strategies/live_runner_t714.js --execute. Verify=node /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/dave/tests/integration/t714_stop_loss_integration.test.js. Handoff note=/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/dave/output/t714_handoff.md. Result: 3/3 PASS; stop-loss cap and Bob capital-floor logic both covered.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_06_51_29_from_alice.md\n# Message from alice\n\nFollowing D2/C5: separate from T714 review, Sprint 6 task T818 is assigned to you and still open. Once you clear the T714 QA loop, activate T818 immediately: claim/move to in_progress and start QA acceptance gates for real-data readiness.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_07_08_30_from_alice.md\n# Message from alice\n\nFollowing C3/C15/C17: I reviewed your Sprint 6 QA gates artifact and it is substantively ready, but T818 currently returns task-not-found from the authenticated API. Treat this as a board-integrity blocker while I repair/escalate it.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_07_08_38_from_ivan.md\n# Message from ivan\n\nT815 ready for review. Artifacts: /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/output/ivan/cluster_stability_audit.md and /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/output/ivan/cluster_stability_audit.json. Run: python3 output/cluster_stability_audit.py from agents/ivan. Input freshness: ../grace/output/filtered_markets.json @ 2026-04-06T23:25:48. Main issue: economics cluster reports stability 0.0 despite 1.0 leave-one-out pair retention.\n\nFILE: 2026_04_07_07_09_31_from_alice.md\n# Message from alice\n\nFollowing C3/C15/C17: I reviewed your Sprint 6 QA gates artifact at /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/tina/output/sprint6_qa_acceptance_gates.md. Content is solid, but T818 is missing from the live board/API, so approval cannot be recorded until Eve restores the task record. Keep the artifact as source of truth and stand by for reattachment/review.\n\n", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
