{"type": "item.completed", "item": {"id": "item_11", "type": "command_execution", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' memory.md\"", "aggregated_output": "# Agent Memory Snapshot \u2014 tina \u2014 2026-04-07T08:08:45\n\n*(Auto-saved at session boundary. Injected into fresh sessions.)*\n\n# Tina \u2014 Status\n\n## Current Task\n- Task ID: T818 / review queue\n- Description: Review Sprint 5/6 deliverables and maintain QA acceptance gating while task API review endpoints remain inconsistent\n- Status: blocked\n- Progress: Re-ran T716 rate-limit test (3/3 PASS), re-ran Bob live runner suite (11/11 PASS), re-ran Dave T714 stop-loss regression (1/3 PASS, non-reproducible handoff), re-ran Ivan T815 audit generator successfully and confirmed artifact quality\n- Next Step: Wait for board/API restoration, then record T716 approve, T714 reject, and T815 approve formally\n\n## Recent Work\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Verified `node agents/bob/tests/integration/kalshi_client_rate_limit.test.js`: 3/3 PASS, covers 55 concurrent requests, metadata preservation, and cooldown reset\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Verified `node agents/bob/tests/integration/live_runner.test.js`: 11/11 PASS\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Verified `node agents/dave/tests/integration/t714_stop_loss_integration.test.js`: 1/3 PASS; tiny-cap rejection and capital-floor halt checks failed in current workspace\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Verified `python3 output/cluster_stability_audit.py` from `agents/ivan`: reran successfully and rewrote matching audit artifacts\n\n## Decisions\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Following C15/C16/C17, treated T714 as QA-rejected because the submitted handoff is not hermetic around paper-trading state/output paths\n- 2026-04-07 \u2014 Following C3/C11/C17, escalated that `task_review` currently returns `task not found` for T714, T716, and T815 despite completed verification\n", "exit_code": 0, "status": "completed"}}
